Introduction to financial environment. Money and its value. Analysis of securities. Bank services. Financial investments.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide the essential terminology and knowledge about the financial environment, and improve mathematical analysis capability for solving simple monetary situations encountered in the financial environment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the subjects and distribution of the financial environment; 2) applies the time value of money in solving the tasks; 3) assesses the value, return, and risk of securities; 4) knows the terminology and services provided of commercial banking; 5) knows the terminology and services provided of investment banking; 6) solves simple monetary situations encountered in commercial banking mathematically in Excel; 7) assesses financial investment returns, costs, profits, profitability, and taxes.
